The paper discusses a detection scheme for uplink massive MIMO, which involves the use of multiple antennas to increase data rates. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves simulations of the proposed algorithm in various application scenarios, which could fall under the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the proposed algorithm, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
